 According to reports, staff members at Wimpy were sitting at the tables when the suspects entered the store.
Minutes later, a devastating blast took place, wiping out most of the shop.  According to Sergeant KC Mac Donald, Belfast SAPS media spokesperson, the group consisted of four armed men in balaclavas.
The ATM was severely damaged by the blast. Fortunately, no one sustained any injuries. This incident followed the blasting of an ATM in Pullenshope, by a single day.  The ATM was situated in a shopping centre in Pullenshope where two suspects blew it up in broad daylight. Warrent Officer David Mbenekazi, told www.mobserver.co.za that the suspects appeared to be inexperienced and the ATM also sustained damages to the degree that nothing could be taken.      Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za